# Found - AI Matchmaking Dating App

AI matchmaking app for serious partnerships. Voice-first onboarding with 10 open-ended questions. AI extracts structured profiles via Whisper + GPT. Matching with dealbreakers and preference checklists.

## Tech Stack

- React Native + Expo SDK 54, Expo Router (file-based routing)
- Convex (real-time backend, no migrations)
- Clerk (phone/SMS auth)
- OpenAI API (gpt-5-mini-2025-08-07)
- MMKV v3 + Zustand (offline storage)
- TypeScript, Bun (package manager)

## Project Structure

```
app/                    # Expo Router screens
├── index.tsx           # Landing page (pre-auth)
├── _layout.tsx         # Root layout with AuthGate, fonts, splash
├── (auth)/             # sign-in.tsx, verify.tsx
├── (onboarding)/       # gender.tsx, sexuality.tsx, location.tsx, birthday.tsx, height.tsx, photos.tsx, relationship-goals.tsx, kids.tsx, wants-kids.tsx, religion.tsx, politics.tsx, substances.tsx, voice-questions.tsx
├── (tabs)/             # index.tsx, questions.tsx, matches.tsx, journey.tsx (hidden)
└── profile.tsx
convex/                 # Backend: schema, mutations, queries, actions
components/             # Reusable UI components
lib/                    # Utilities, theme, matching algorithm
hooks/                  # Custom React hooks
stores/                 # Zustand stores
```

## Critical Conventions

- **Convex does NOT auto-sync.** After ANY change to `convex/` files, run `bunx convex dev` to push.
- Always reference questions by `questionKey`, never by `order` number.
- All screens use `useEffectiveUserId()` instead of `useAuth()` directly (supports dev impersonation).
- Env: `EXPO_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `EXPO_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL` in `.env.local`; `OPENAI_API_KEY` set via `bunx convex env set`.

## Running the App

```bash
bun install
bunx convex dev          # Keep running in separate terminal
bun start                # Press 'i' for iOS simulator
```
